<p class="p">We first initialize the analysis in each country with the observed per capita GDP from the starting year 
 <italic class="italic">t</italic> = 0 of the socioeconomic data (e.g., 
 <italic class="italic">GDPcap</italic>
 <sub class="sub">
  <italic class="italic">Obs</italic>
 </sub>[1961]). Then, for each year 
 <italic class="italic">t</italic> and using the temperature–growth response functions 
 <italic class="italic">f</italic> estimated above, we calculate the difference in growth rate between the observed temperature and the counterfactual temperature (
 <xref ref-type="fig" rid="fig01" class="xref">Fig. 1 
  <italic class="italic">C</italic> and 
  <italic class="italic">D</italic>
 </xref>):
 <disp-formula id="uneq3" class="disp-formula">
  <math id="me3" class="math">
   <mrow class="mrow">
    <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">Δ</mi>
    <mi mathvariant="italic" class="mi">Growth</mi>
    <mrow class="mrow">
     <mo class="mo">[</mo>
     <mi class="mi">t</mi>
     <mo class="mo">]</mo>
    </mrow>
    <mo class="mo">=</mo>
    <mi class="mi">f</mi>
    <mrow class="mrow">
     <mo class="mo">(</mo>
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <msub class="msub">
       <mi class="mi">T</mi>
       <mrow class="mrow">
        <mi mathvariant="italic" class="mi">NoAnthro</mi>
       </mrow>
      </msub>
      <mrow class="mrow">
       <mo class="mo">[</mo>
       <mi class="mi">t</mi>
       <mo class="mo">]</mo>
      </mrow>
     </mrow>
     <mo class="mo">)</mo>
    </mrow>
    <mo class="mo">−</mo>
    <mi class="mi">f</mi>
    <mrow class="mrow">
     <mo class="mo">(</mo>
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <msub class="msub">
       <mi class="mi">T</mi>
       <mrow class="mrow">
        <mi mathvariant="italic" class="mi">Obs</mi>
       </mrow>
      </msub>
      <mrow class="mrow">
       <mo class="mo">[</mo>
       <mi class="mi">t</mi>
       <mo class="mo">]</mo>
      </mrow>
     </mrow>
     <mo class="mo">)</mo>
    </mrow>
    <mo class="mo">.</mo>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </disp-formula>
</p>
